    <p>The new hirings I was part of were done with the idea of shifting the culture into a <strong>more user-centric approach</strong>, bringing design closer to business and the rest of stakeholders.</p>
    <p>To kickstart this <strong>cultural shift</strong> and establish some <strong>understanding of the design process</strong>, I created a document including a series of flows. These flows would propose deliverables, touch-points and actors involved in the different stages of the design process.</p>
    <p>These stages weren't meant to be followed to the detail, but they set a standard and specified some loops of work in which internal stakeholders would know what came next. Also they <strong>improved the general communication with the stakeholders</strong> and raised visibility of the design work.</p>  
