  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>Documenting the work</h2>
    <p>Design work includes many documents of very different nature: mock-ups, prototypes, slideshows, flows, matrices, heatmaps, surveysâ€¦ As parts of the efforts for establishing a design process within Devex, we have worked in how we document and manage design assets.</p>
    <p>Previously most design UI assets were exported as images and stored in Google Drive as folders pertaining to each different project and organised by dates and author. That made it quite hard to know whether some designs or resarches were already available. We took the initiative of making <strong>Figma our only source of truth</strong>:</p>
    <p>It is not only the reference point to all the information regarding mock-ups allowing us to easily isolate the different proposals, but also where we link our research documents or where we gather most of the initial feedback , as well as discussions related to specific jira tasks later in the development process.</p>
    <p>With all this in mind, I tried to come up with a <strong>structure for our Figma documents</strong>. Unsurprisingly, it has evolved with the time to better accommodate our needs or adapting to the nature of each project, and the improvements we keep adding to our process.</p>
