  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>Conclusions</h2>
    <p>Through this process we have achieved several outcomes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>While there are still areas for improvement in communication, the <strong>understanding of design work</strong> has notably <strong>improved</strong>.</li>
      <li>By working on actionable items and setting iterations, we have been able to achieve <strong>more consistent delivery</strong>.</li>
      <li>Design <strong>feedback</strong> now happens organically and <strong>asynchronously, improving efficiency</strong>.</li>
      <li>All <strong>design assets are centralized</strong> within the <strong>Figma</strong> team project and organised according to our platform structure.</li>
      <li>Overall and in alignment with the work done in the <a href="https://apedraza.net/case-study/devex-design-system/" data-type="link" data-id="https://apedraza.net/case-study/devex-design-system/">internal Design System</a>, the <strong>delivery speed</strong> of the design team has <strong>increased drastically</strong>.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>While we have walked a long distance from where we started, the work is far from done. I'm glad of the improvements and grateful for all the people involved in the evolution of this process.</p>
  </section>
